    "description": "<div><b>PD Gazette - March 2022</b></div><div>Old-Fashioned Romance Number</div><div><br /></div><div>Beginning with an intriguing western recently added to the Project Gutenberg library, here is a collection of public domain romantic tales first published up through 1926.\u00a0 In non-fiction, there is the title essay by Harry Emerson Fosdick from his 1926 book, <i>Adventurous Religion</i>, a luncheon menu from <i>A Thousand Ways To Please A Husband</i>, and a couple of short 'etchings' from <i>Short Stories</i> magazine.\u00a0 I adapted works by Ellen Glasgow and George Kibbe Turner with more modern language to make them a little more accessible; while the Glasgow tale is pretty camp Southern belle stuff, the Turner story is a fun adventure-in-Italy (think Hayley Mills in the 60's) ideal for teen girls. Prosper M\u00e9rim\u00e9e's <i>Mateo Facone</i> is considered France's first published short story.\u00a0</div>",
